defs.name: lerp
defs.value: pub fn lerp(Self, Self, F) -> Self
defs.docs: Interpolate and extrapolate between `self` and `other` using `t` as the parameter.

attributes.value: / Interpolate and extrapolate between `self` and `other` using `t` as the parameter.
/ At `t == 0.0`, the result is equal to `self`.
/ At `t == 1.0`, the result is equal to `other`.
/ At all other points, the result is a mix of `self` and `other`, proportional to `t`.
/ `t` is unbounded, so extrapolation and negative interpolation are no problem.
